                           <div class="entire_tip">
<div class="tip_number">TIP 4</div>
<div class="tip_contents">
            If you have the symptoms of nausea (possibly with vomiting), headache, and fatigue, consider that you may have carbon monoxide poisoning, especially if you feel worse indoors and someone you live with is experiencing similar symptoms. Other possible symptoms include bright red gums and lips, cherry red skin, weakness, mental confusion, dilated pupils, and/or chest pain (particularly if you are elderly). It is crucial to evacuate the house or the car and seek medical treatment.
        </div>

</div>
